sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M45802
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Mutated Tuc2009 bidirectional promoter for decreased CI sensitivity
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A modified bi-directional promoter from lactococcal bacteriophage Tuc2009 containing a bp mutation for decreased binding affinity of the CI repressor protein to the operator OL-CI at high CI concentrations. Allowing for continued up-regulated transcription from the leftward promoter (PL). See BBa_M45801 for detailed description of bi-directional promoter and intergenic switch region regulation with CI and Cro repressor proteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Thomas Overbeck
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Kenny JG, Leach S, Hoz AB, Venema G, Kok J, Fitzgerald GF, Nauta S, Alonso JC, Sinderen D (2006) Characterization of the lytic-lysogenic switch of the lactococcal bacteriophage Tuc2009. Virology 347:434-446
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: G to T change at bp 32 from BBa_M45801 on Fwd strand

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M45805

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kaitlyn C. Anderson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This sequence has been codon optimized for Lactococcus lactis

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B1006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Artificial terminator, estimated %T~>90% *8bp stem, 6nt loop *Bidirectional, estimated reverse %T~>90%
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Haiyao Huang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: modified E. coli thr terminator, replaced all A-T pairs in stem with C-G pairs
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Bidirectional, with the reverse estimated to be less effective than the forward. Has a polyA tail of 9 residues.
